info.report-description: VLR measurement, part n, paging per LAC(PPLAC)

kpi_info.title: period_duration
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: VOICE_PAGING_PER_LAC_ATTEMPT
kpi_info.use: The counter is updated when MSC sends first Paging message on A-interface and the reason of the paging is mobile terminated voice call. The repagings are not counted.There are certain cases (ie. single numbering scheme) when the call type (speech or data call) cannot be determined during the paging process. These pagings are considered as voice paging regarding this counter.Doesn't contain the cases when the paging result is subscriber busy.

kpi_info.title: VOICE_PAGING_PER_LAC_SUCCESS
kpi_info.use: The counter is updated when MSC receives Paging Response message on A-interface and the reason of the paging was mobile terminated voice call.There are certain cases (ie. single numbering scheme) when the call type (speech or data) cannot be determined during the paging process. These pagings are considered as voice paging regarding this counter.Doesn't contain the cases when the paging result is subscriber busy.

kpi_info.title: DATAMISSINGINPAGINGPERLA
kpi_info.use: Not in use. This line is printed if datatransfer from one or several VLRUs failed during one or more inquiries, that is, only a subset of the data could be collected. It means that the printed counters per LAC are not reliable. (The problem can be overloaded VLRUs, a VLRU start-up.)

kpi_info.title: PAGINGATTEMPTPERLA
kpi_info.use: Not in use. Number of initiated pagingsfrom the VLR to the specific LA. This counter contains the paging of both Normal and Telemetric subscribers. Searchings, PS domain pagings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging.

kpi_info.title: PAGINGSUCCPERLA
kpi_info.use: Not in use. Number of successful pagingsin VLR in the specific LA. This counter contains the paging of both Normal and Telemetric subscribers. Searchings, PS domain pagings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging.

kpi_info.title: PAGINGATTEMPTWITHIMSISUCC
kpi_info.use: Not in use. The number of paging attemptwith IMSI for successful pagings (ATT#(SUCC)) counters show how many paging requests were sent to the A and Iu interfaces (from MSC) per LAC when the paging was successful. This counter contains the paging of both Normal and Telemetric subscribers. Searchings, PS domain pagings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging.

kpi_info.title: PAGINGATTEMPTWITHTMSISUCC
kpi_info.use: Not in use. The number of paging attemptwith TMSI for successful pagings (ATT#(SUCC)) counters show how many paging requests were sent to the A and Iu interfaces (from MSC) per LAC when the paging was successful. This counter contains the paging of both Normal and Telemetric subscribers. Searchings, PS domain pagings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging.

kpi_info.title: PAGINGATTEMPTWITHIMSIFAIL
kpi_info.use: Not in use. The number of paging attemptwith IMSI for failed pagings (ATT#(FAIL)) counters show how many paging requests were sent to the A and Iu interfaces (from MSC) per LAC when the paging failed. This counter contains the paging of both Normal and Telemetric subscribers. Searchings, PS domain pagings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging.

kpi_info.title: PAGINGATTEMPTWITHTMSIFAIL
kpi_info.use: Not in use. The number of paging attemptwith TMSI for failed pagings (ATT#(FAIL)) counters show how many paging requests were sent to the A and Iu interfaces (from MSC) per LAC when the paging failed. This counter contains the paging of both Normal and Telemetric subscribers. Searchings, PS domain pagings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging.

kpi_info.title: ANSWERTIME
kpi_info.use: Not in use. The average time betweenthe last paging request message and the corresponding paging response (during a paging) is shown in the ANS.TIME field in tenth of second. If there is not any successful paging this counter is not applicable.

kpi_info.title: PAG_1ST_VOICE_TMSI_ATT
kpi_info.use: This counter shows the number of paging attempts with TMSI per Location Area, which have been sent out the first time on A, IU, Gs or SGs interface during paging procedure for voice and data calls. NOTE1: Data calls are also included - in spite of the naming of the counter. NOTE2: PSI pagings, PSI pre-pagings and PRN-pre-pagings are also included. NOTE3: LCS pagings are not included. This counter contains the paging of both normal and telemetric subscribers. Searchings are not included in this counter. This counter is not updated when the subscriber is busy during the paging. Pre-pagings are included as well. Measured object: The measured object is the Location Area Code (LAC).

kpi_info.use: This counter shows the number of successful pagings with IMSI per Location Area, which have been sent out the fifth time on A, IU, Gs or SGs interface during paging procedure for SMS. This counter contains the paging of both normal and telemetric subscribers. Searchings are not included in this counter. Counter is not updated when MT-SMS is made during an ongoing call or in case of USSD paging. Measured object: The measured object is the Location Area Code (LAC).
